		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=216942"><span id=>Rotcgok</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>20 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>First I would like to say that I am not an expert on all that is paladin, but I can say that 95% of people that group with me come back asking for more because I am that damn good.&nbsp;&nbsp;My pally is currently 57, 3047 hp, 1197 ac unbuffed.  I hope thats good.  I'd like an opinion, I'm working on getting a full suit of Royal Attendant gear from North Ro.  Is it worth it?  My guild, Feral Redemption is slowly but surely making its way into the high level dungeons and the planes.  Hell, we're taking Vindi down on a regular basis, we raid almost every night.  The question is, is Royal Attendant good enough to hold me over until better armor comes along?  Also I need a new 2HS, my 1HS, 1HB, 2HB weapons are all damn good.  My 2HS is good, but it just ain't cuttin' it.  I have a Tae Ew 2 Hander for 2HS.  What should I try to obtain to replace this?  Now for some tips to the younger pallies.  At mid and higher levels, you will hold agro by using spells.  By spells I mean our bread and butter, stuns.  I use a combination of Holy Might, Force, Quellious' Words of Tranquility, Flame of Light(though it isn't a stun) and Thunder of Karana on caster mobs.  I don't always use every one of these or in any particular order, but i tend to use Flame of Light and Holy Might the most since they tend to stick more often for me, I really don't get that seeing as how QWoT and Force are higher level spells than both but thats what works for me.  So at lower levels, start using your stuns and getting used to them.  They are your bread and butter.  Avoid using Flash of Light too much.  MOBs will run unless they're snared or rooted.  It got me into a lot of trouble at earlier levels.  Also never mistake yourself for a cleric.  Had a friend that quit the game for Galaxies, his paladin was 46 when he quit.  He thought he was a cleric with a sword.  However, I did do a BB adventure this morning just before patch with me as MH, warrior as MT, 2 rangers, a beastlord and an enchanter.  We had 1 death in all, the enchanter, died when mezz broke once early in dungeon.  We even finished the dungeon with about 10 minutes left.  Wow, I need to create a cleric with my healing skills.  If any of you young or even experienced paladins have questions, just post a reply to this post and I'll try to answer em for you.<br><br>Rotcgok Ringu<br>Knight of Marr<br>PROUD member of Feral Redemption<br>Morell-Thule<br>&quot;Expect to Win.&quot;<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed May  5 10:56:34 2004</em></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Rotcgok Ringu<br>PROUD member of Feral Redemption and very PROUD of HIS MEMBER<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1027023&resize=true" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1027023&resize=true</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
